subSection.paragraph:
Chirotica species
are characterized morphologically by having the genal carina reaching the hypostomal carina above the base of mandible, center of face elevated into a tubercle, clypeus wide and moderately convex, mandibular teeth pointed and of equal sizes, areolet absent, posterior transverse carina of the mesosternum complete, propodeum with entire areas, and areas superomedia and basalis generally confluent ( Townes 1970 ; Kanhekar 1989 ). As far as currently recorded, they are idiobiont ectoparasitoids parasitoids of larvae or pupae of Psychidae ( Lepidoptera ) ( Kanhekar 1989 ;
Mifsud et al . 2019
).

