Diagnosis.

Chirotica nigra


sp. nov.

can be distinguished from all other Neotropical 

Chirotica
species

by the combination of the following characters: 
(1)
antenna with a brownish-brown median band and blackish-brown apex (
Fig. 26A
); 
(2)
pronotal collar yellowish-orange (
Fig. 26A
); 
(3)
mesoscutum with matted areas posterolateral (
Fig. 26D
); 
(4)
tergites 2 and 3 with punctuation and smooth on central part (
Fig. 26E
).

