Diagnosis.

Chirotica pothina

can be distinguished from all other Neotropical 

Chirotica
species

by the combination of the following characters: 
(1)
antenna with a reddish-brown median band and blackened apex (
Fig 29A
); 
(2)
pronotal collar black (
Fig 29A
); 
(3)
region between posterior ocelli with weak rugae and punctuation (
Fig 29B
); 
(4)
tergites 2 and 3 with medial punctuation and lateral rugae (
Fig 29E
).

